defs.docs:
A library that makes linear color calculations and conversion easy and
 accessible for anyone. It uses the type system to enforce correctness and
 to avoid mistakes, such as mixing incompatible color types.

defs.name: blend
defs.docs: Color blending and blending equations.

defs.name: Equations
defs.docs: A pair of blending equations and corresponding parameters.

defs.name: color_equation
defs.docs: The equation for the color components.

defs.name: alpha_equation
defs.docs: The equation for the alpha component.

defs.name: color_parameters
defs.docs: The parameters for the color components.

defs.name: alpha_parameters
defs.docs: The parameters for the alpha component.

defs.name: from_equations
defs.docs:
Create a pair of blending equations, where all the parameters are
`One`.

defs.name: from_parameters
defs.docs:
Create a pair of additive blending equations with the provided
parameters.

defs.name: Add
defs.docs: Add the source and destination, according to `sp * S + dp * D`.

defs.name: Subtract
defs.docs:
Subtract the destination from the source, according to `sp * S - dp *
 D`.

defs.name: ReverseSubtract
defs.docs:
Subtract the source from the destination, according to `dp * D - sp *
 S`.

defs.name: Min
defs.docs:
Create a color where each component is the smallest of each of the
source and destination components. A.k.a. component wise min. The
parameters are ignored.

defs.name: Max
defs.docs:
Create a color where each component is the largest of each of the
source and destination components. A.k.a. component wise max. The
parameters are ignored.

defs.name: Equation
defs.docs: A blending equation.

defs.name: Parameters
defs.docs: A pair of source and destination parameters.

defs.docs: The source parameter.

defs.name: destination

defs.name: One
defs.docs: A simple 1.

defs.name: Zero

defs.name: OneMinusSourceColor
defs.docs: One minus the source color, or alpha.

defs.name: DestinationColor
defs.docs: The destination color, or alpha.

defs.name: OneMinusDestinationColor
defs.docs: One minus the destination color, or alpha.

defs.name: SourceAlpha
defs.docs: The source alpha.

defs.name: OneMinusSourceAlpha
defs.docs: One minus the source alpha.

defs.name: DestinationAlpha

defs.name: alpha
defs.docs:
The transparency component. 0.0 is fully transparent and 1.0 is fully

defs.name: Blend
defs.docs: A trait for colors that can be blended together.

defs.name: Color

defs.name: from_premultiplied
defs.docs: Convert the color from premultiplied alpha.

defs.name: blend
defs.value: fn <F> (self, destination: Self, blend_function: F) -> Self
defs.docs:
Blend self, as the source color, with `destination`, using
`blend_function`. Anything that implements `BlendFunction` is
acceptable, including functions and closures.

defs.name: over
defs.docs:
Place `self` over `other`. This is the good old common alpha
composition equation.

defs.name: inside
defs.docs:
Results in the parts of `self` that overlaps the visible parts of
`other`.

defs.name: outside
defs.docs:
Results in the parts of `self` that lies outside the visible parts of
`other`.

defs.name: atop
defs.docs: Place `self` over only the visible parts of `other`.

defs.name: xor
defs.docs: Results in either `self` or `other`, where they do not overlap.

defs.name: plus
defs.docs:
Add `self` and `other`. This uses the alpha component to regulate the
effect, so it's not just plain component wise addition.

defs.name: multiply
defs.docs:
Multiply `self` with `other`. This uses the alpha component to regulate
the effect, so it's not just plain component wise multiplication.

defs.name: screen
defs.docs: Make a color which is at least as light as `self` or `other`.

defs.name: overlay
defs.docs:
Multiply `self` or `other` if other is dark, or screen them if `other`
is light. This results in an S curve.

defs.name: darken
defs.docs: Return the darkest parts of `self` and `other`.

defs.name: lighten
defs.docs: Return the lightest parts of `self` and `other`.

defs.name: dodge
defs.docs:
Lighten `other` to reflect `self`. Results in `other` if `self` is
black.

defs.name: burn
defs.docs:
Darken `other` to reflect `self`. Results in `other` if `self` is
white.

defs.name: hard_light
defs.docs:
Multiply `self` or `other` if other is dark, or screen them if `self`
is light. This is similar to `overlay`, but depends on `self` instead
of `other`.

defs.name: soft_light
defs.docs:
Lighten `other` if `self` is light, or darken `other` as if it's burned
if `self` is dark. The effect is increased if the components of `self`
is further from 0.5.

defs.name: difference
defs.docs:
Return the absolute difference between `self` and `other`. It's
basically `abs(self - other)`, but regulated by the alpha component.

defs.name: exclusion
defs.docs:
Similar to `difference`, but appears to result in a lower contrast.
`other` is inverted if `self` is white, and preserved if `self` is
black.

defs.name: BlendFunction
defs.docs: A trait for custom blend functions.

defs.name: apply_to
defs.value: fn (self, source: PreAlpha<C, C::Scalar>, destination: PreAlpha<C, C::Scalar>) -> PreAlpha<C, C::Scalar>
defs.docs: Apply this blend function to a pair of colors.

defs.name: gradient
defs.docs: Types for interpolation between multiple colors.

defs.name: Gradient
defs.docs: A linear interpolation between colors.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Create a gradient of evenly spaced colors with the domain [0.0, 1.0].
There must be at least one color.

defs.name: with_domain
defs.docs:
Create a gradient of colors with custom spacing and domain. There must be
at least one color and they are expected to be ordered by their
position value.

defs.name: get
defs.docs:
Get a color from the gradient. The color of the closest control point
will be returned if `i` is outside the domain.

defs.name: take
defs.docs: Take `n` evenly spaced colors from the gradient, as an iterator.

defs.name: slice
defs.docs: Slice this gradient to limit its domain.

defs.name: domain
defs.docs: Get the limits of this gradient's domain.

defs.name: Take
defs.docs: An iterator over interpolated colors.

defs.name: Slice
defs.docs: A slice of a Gradient that limits its domain.

defs.name: get
defs.docs:
Get a color from the gradient slice. The color of the closest domain
limit will be returned if `i` is outside the domain.

defs.name: take
defs.docs: Take `n` evenly spaced colors from the gradient slice, as an iterator.

defs.name: slice
defs.docs:
Slice this gradient slice to further limit its domain. Ranges outside
the domain will be clamped to the nearest domain limit.

defs.name: domain
defs.docs: Get the limits of this gradient slice's domain.

defs.name: Range
defs.docs: A domain range for gradient slices.

defs.name: named
defs.docs:
A collection of named color constants. Can be toggled with the `"named"` and `"named_from_str"`
Cargo features.

The whiteness of the color. It specifies the amount white to mix into
 the hue. It varies from 0 to 1, with 1 being always full white and 0
always being the color shade (a mixture of a pure hue with black)
 chosen with the other two controls.

 the hue. It varies from 0 to 1, with 1 being always full black and
 0 always being the color tint (a mixture of a pure hue with white)
 chosen with the other two
